🧩 Problem: Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array

You are given an integer array nums sorted in non-decreasing order.

Your task is to remove the duplicates in-place, such that:

Each unique element appears only once
The relative order of elements remains the same

🎯 What should you return?

Return an integer k such that:

The first k elements of nums contain the unique elements
The rest of the array doesn’t matter

🔍 Example
Input:
nums = [1, 1, 2, 2, 3]

After removing duplicates:
nums = [1, 2, 3, _, _]

First k = 3 elements are unique
_ means values beyond k are irrelevant

Solution:
class Solution {
fun removeDuplicates(nums: IntArray): Int {
    if(nums.size == 0) return 0
    var i = 0
    var j = 1
    while(j < nums.size){
        if(nums[i] != nums[j]){
            i++
            nums[i] = nums[j]
        }
        j++
    }
   return i+1
    }
}
